HEADWORD: Open-eyed
<hw>O"pen-eyed`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>With eyes widely
open; alert to possible danger; watchful; vigilant.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> argus-eyed, hawk-eyed, unsleeping, vigilant, wary,
watchful.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>  + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

